<br>
Change it to ratio 7<br>
Keep the damage cap, lack of crits<br>
Remove the manaburn-per-minute, and make it every 5 seconds.<br>
<br>
or<br>
<br>
Change manaburn to take 2400 mana, not the whole bar, doing 9600 damage, and having the same low aggro.<br>
<br>
Consider for a minute wha 12 wizards all manaburn with old rules would do to a mob like Coirnarv. He has such low HPs that he'd be some sorta smudge really fast at some point(what, 100k hps total?). Super-low hp mobs that could be MB trivialized though really dont last long enough to be trivialized by a MB every 5 seconds. This way, lower mana wizards could drop MBs into a mob towards the end of the fight. Though, if an EP fight is looking bad, I'm out of mana significantly before fight end- generally in the learning period that accompanies those mobs before you get them flawless.<br>
<br>
as it stands, manaburn is almost entirely useless. there are a few niche uses and those are very few. if VI really cares to make manaburn a decent ability, some changes need to be made to it. this AA can be used with a VERY long recharge time, and usually is detrimental. Compared to trueshot, it's like 10 seconds of good bow damage and then being only able to punch the mob. It severely lowers your damage. it may as well be the act of valor of wizardry without the healing part.<br>
<br>
if Manaburn is to be made a useful ability, this is an example of what needs to be done to it. while it is usually useless, there's nothing about class balance that really begs this ability to be fixed up. it's like ranger trueshot- dont tell me thats a balanced ability because the dmg increase is ridiculous... but theres a big timer on it and you lose WS if you trueshot so it's a tack-on ability and has nothing to do with the class balance really. I remember a funny story, in solusek tower all of a guild's rangers decided to trueshot on a miniboss - these are totally trivial mobs - and when they did solusek ro the guild had nobody with weaponshield up for Solusek Ro. That's an example of when you'd be better off without it, as the rangers could all AFK and the guild beat a sol mini, but then they add the complication of Weaponshield.<br>
<br>
Personally I'd like us to have a decent manaburn. What is the point of this ability as it stands? It has none! If the developers think it's actually useful, they are deluding themselves. Should it be part of their `plan` to have a useless AA skill, that's fine with me but I don't understand it. In my opinion, any developer resource devoted to something that is useless(other classes have useless AAs, too) is wasted effort. The significance of a useful manaburn to me is that I would actually get the AA. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=remfin>Remfin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Suffers from Hypocriteria</span><br>  Posts: 1582<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 4:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh</span><hr size=1> &quot;Consider for a minute wha 12 wizards all manaburn with old rules would do to a mob like Coirnarv. He has such low HPs that he'd be some sorta smudge really fast at some point(what, 100k hps total?).&quot;<br>
