There is a very small amount of mobs that are resistant to every type (magic/cold/fire) of our damage, and even just nuking with PoP lures is still way more effecient, let alone SoS, ISoS, and Draughts.  Any fight that doesn't last long enough so that you can't do enough damage regularly is trivial anyways and you probably shouldn't be wasting your whole mana bar on it.  Not unless you've got nothing else to do... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khaelwizzie>khaelwizzie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 8:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Concussion works when resisted.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I know people believe this because you get agro off a resisted nuke. But you don't get the benefits of that nuke (i.e. the damage). Same with resisted concussions.. you get the agro from casting a spell on the mob, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>but you don't get the benefit</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Chances are, if you're experiencing less agro while casting concussions on a 100% MR mob, that's because there's more time between your nukes, spaced out by recast times and casting time for concussion, not because concussion is actually working when resisting.<br>
