<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The only thing I see going for manaburn is that it is unresistable if you won't be able to land anything else.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I just shake my head at all these people advocating you to manaburn early and med back up to full, using all the mana regen items/buffs you can get as their excuse. On practically every mob in the game, even those requiring lures, you would do loads more damage just nuking regularly with that full manapool. And with all that mana regen you can maintain enough mana to keep nuking regularly for more damage longer, then med up back to full. Only difference is people are either lazy and don't want to be doing all the damage they can do, or they're incapable of managing their aggro. If you're not capable of managing aggro, you shouldn't be a wizard. Go play a paladin or a ranger or something.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ok, let's look at the benefits of Mana Burn.  <br>
1) Produces nearly zero aggro.<br>
2) Nearly unresistable, even from a distance on mobs normally requiring melee range to lands spells on.<br>
3) Super fast DPS.  No other spell in the game produces 1300+ DPS besides Shadow Knight AA improved HT.<br>
<br>
The downside?  It makes you OoM.<br>
<br>
Therefore, I think it is more than reasonable to say that if you can manage to minimize the downside of using the ability, the benefits are VERY justified.  However, this is probably only plausible if you are in a mostly level 65 raid force (for buffs, etc.) have decent gear and AA abilities, and coordinate your efforts adequetely.<br>
<br>
Let's do some math-<br>
<br>
Let's assume it is my personal responsibility in this fight to deliver 45k damage to the target (at least).<br>
<br>
Using standard nuking and aggro control, I can manage 150 dps by casting Draught of Ro, with a Concussion cast after every other Draught.  I.E. I will net 1235 damage on average (after adjustments for crits and focus) every 8 seconds.  This will get me 45k damage in 292 seconds with 36 casts of Draught of Ro and is reasonablly safe aggro-wise.  I will need to delay my nuking for about 20 seconds, however, to allow the MT to establish aggro on the mob and ensure the healers are going to keep him alive.  in other words, in 5.2 minutes I will fulfill my &quot;quota&quot; and deliver 45k damage.  In doing so I will burn through roughly 5k mana, which means I will have a large surplus left over at the end of the fight due to mana regeneration.<br>
<br>
Using Mana burn I can deliver 9k damage IMMEDIATELY, Harvest / Harvest of Druzzil / Mod Rod / Etc. and THEN nuke as I would normally.  Once I start nuking I will deal the remaining 36k damage to fulfill my &quot;quota&quot; in about 232 seconds.<br>
<br>
Basically, by using Mana Burn I will successfully deliver the 45k damage I was responsible for AN ENTIRE MINUTE SOONER, 20% faster in a fight that usually runs 5 minutes long.  In other words, someone NOT using Mana Burn will do the damage I do in 1.24 the amount of time I do.  An entire minute is a pretty long time when you are engaging mobs that triple hit for 2k+ damage.<br>
<br>
Some of you may claim you do more than 45k damage on your fights, but in these instances you probablly should not be using Mana Burn.  But even in these cases, if you have a good free right-click nuke item, or have remarkable mana regeneration (Flowing Thought, horse, etc), using Mana Burn can be beneficial.  In the example above the difference in DPS is 179 DPS with Mana Burn compared to 144 DPS without.  Both of these numbers are rather conservative in my opinion, and could certainly be increased with harder nuking under most circumstances.  The benefit of Mana Burn is that it is fast, reliable, and aggro free.  In shorter fights the DPS it allows simply can't be beat if you can maximize it's effectiveness while minimizing it's downside.  It was not designed for marathon fights where the Wizard is responsible for delivering 100k damage to the target. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=27065.topic&start=21&stop=22>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=27065.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=27065.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=27065.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=27065.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUn